moves, you know that?

1499
01:17:47,696 --> 01:17:48,429
You don't think
I know who that guy is?

1500
01:17:49,798 --> 01:17:52,400
Where he works,
what he does? Hmm?

1501
01:17:52,402 --> 01:17:54,268
You don't think I know
what you're trying to do?

1502
01:17:55,704 --> 01:17:57,405
You're done, Richie.

1503
01:17:57,407 --> 01:18:00,074
I think you should just walk
outside and get in my car.

1504
01:18:00,076 --> 01:18:02,243
There's gotta be some kind
of deal you and I can make.

1505
01:18:02,245 --> 01:18:04,345
Thank you, Richie,
but I'm well taken care of.

1506
01:18:04,347 --> 01:18:07,014
I think you should
stop embarrassing yourself,

1507
01:18:07,016 --> 01:18:10,151
walk outside, and get in
the motherfucking car, man.

1508
01:18:15,190 --> 01:18:17,758
You don't think
I'm taken care of, too?

1509
01:18:21,296 --> 01:18:22,329
(GRUNTING)
(GROANING)

1510
01:18:30,305 --> 01:18:31,772
(PHONE BEEPS)
(WILSON GROANING)

1511
01:18:34,176 --> 01:18:35,276
<i>SHAVERS: Richie Furst.</i>

1512
01:18:35,278 --> 01:18:37,044
Shavers.

1513
01:18:37,046 --> 01:18:38,646
<i>We found Cronin beat half
to death, but he's alive.</i>

1514
01:18:38,648 --> 01:18:40,281
Thank God.

1515
01:18:40,283 --> 01:18:42,183
<i>Where are you?
Are you bringing me evidence?</i>

1516
01:18:42,185 --> 01:18:44,018
No. I'm bringing
you something better.

1517
01:18:45,320 --> 01:18:47,955
<i>RICHIE: Block
timed it perfectly.</i>

1518
01:18:47,957 --> 01:18:49,390
<i>He's out the door by the
time the bribes stopped</i>

1519
01:18:49,392 --> 01:18:51,192
<i>and the police
took everything down.</i>

1520
01:18:52,928 --> 01:18:54,095
(BRAKES SCREECHING)

1521
01:19:22,758 --> 01:19:24,091
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

1522
01:19:25,627 --> 01:19:26,560
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)
Yeah?

1523
01:19:26,562 --> 01:19:28,329
Hey, Richie.
Where are you?

1524
01:19:28,864 --> 01:19:31,699
At the office.

1525
01:19:31,701 --> 01:19:34,268
Ivan, what the hell is going on?
The site's been frozen.

1526
01:19:34,270 --> 01:19:36,437
<i>IVAN: Listen, Richie, you're
about to get arrested, okay?</i>

1527
01:19:36,439 --> 01:19:38,439
<i>I'd love to tell you that I was gonna
come down to the police station</i>

1528
01:19:38,441 --> 01:19:40,741
<i>and bail you out but we
both know that's not true.</i>

1529
01:19:40,743 --> 01:19:42,076
Sorry it worked out
this way.

1530
01:19:42,078 --> 01:19:44,512
I like you,
you're a good kid.

1531
01:19:44,514 --> 01:19:46,013
But it is what it is.

1532
01:19:46,015 --> 01:19:47,848
<i>Sorry, pal. By.</i>

1533
01:19:50,285 --> 01:19:52,553
(SIGHS) You all right?
Yeah, set.

1534
01:19:52,555 --> 01:19:54,855
You'll find another boyfriend
when we land at the next stop.

1535
01:19:54,857 --> 01:19:56,791
Younger and
dumber next time.

1536
01:19:56,793 --> 01:19:57,792
Dumber won't be easy.

1537
01:20:05,100 --> 01:20:06,066
(THANKS IN SPANISH)

1538
01:20:09,805 --> 01:20:11,172
Where the fuck is Wilson?

1539
01:20:11,174 --> 01:20:12,373
I haven't seen him.

1540
01:20:39,634 --> 01:20:41,035
Let's go. He'll have
to fend for himself.

1541
01:21:04,693 --> 01:21:06,927
Do you mind? Sun.

1542
01:21:08,997 --> 01:21:10,431
(EXHALES)

1543
01:21:10,433 --> 01:21:12,566
I love new beginnings.

1544
01:21:12,568 --> 01:21:14,335
Any new industry,
the first 10 years,

1545
01:21:14,337 --> 01:21:16,303
it's like Russia
after Communism.

1546
01:21:16,305 --> 01:21:18,939
It's all strength
and will.

1547
01:21:18,941 --> 01:21:21,609
And now, it's time for a
little nuance and finesse.

1548
01:21:37,959 --> 01:21:40,394
<i>RICHIE: Every player has
a leak in his game.</i>

1549
01:21:40,396 --> 01:21:42,363
<i>(SIGHS)
Even Block.</i>

1550
01:21:42,365 --> 01:21:44,131
<i>All you have to do
is find it.</i>

1551
01:21:44,133 --> 01:21:46,934
RICHIE: You really saw
me coming, didn't you?

1552
01:21:48,169 --> 01:21:52,806
The cars, the boats,
the money, everything.

1553
01:21:52,808 --> 01:21:55,976
You handpicked me, and you
slow-played it perfectly.

1554
01:21:59,414 --> 01:22:01,515
What did you expect
me to do, Richie?

1555
01:22:01,517 --> 01:22:02,950
Walk into my party,

1556
01:22:02,952 --> 01:22:04,485
accuse me of cheating
in front of all my friends.

1557
01:22:04,487 --> 01:22:06,453
I can't let that go by.

1558
01:22:06,455 --> 01:22:07,621
That's the problem
with your generation.

1559
01:22:07,623 --> 01:22:09,123
You guys sat around
with your vintage T-shirts

1560
01:22:09,125 --> 01:22:10,524
and your participation medals

1561
01:22:10,526 --> 01:22:12,326
and you never did anything.

1562
01:22:12,328 --> 01:22:14,395
And you got too big
and too greedy.

1563
01:22:16,264 --> 01:22:19,233
Okay. What are you
gonna do about it?

1564
01:22:19,235 --> 01:22:21,135
You don't think
I own this place, too?

1565
01:22:23,271 --> 01:22:25,606
And where exactly
do you think this is?

1566
01:22:32,714 --> 01:22:35,849
<i>Bienvenidos
a Puerto RicoIvan!</i>

1567
01:22:35,851 --> 01:22:39,153
Territory of the United
States of America.

1568
01:22:45,927 --> 01:22:48,162
<i>RICHIE: The Captain,
a man of his word.</i>

1569
01:22:50,498 --> 01:22:52,366
I knew deep down
you were just homesick.

1570
01:22:52,368 --> 01:22:54,268
(SIRENS WAILING
IN THE DISTANCE)

1571
01:22:56,204 --> 01:22:58,973
You know what your biggest
problem is, Ivan?

1572
01:22:58,975 --> 01:23:01,842
You talk and you talk, but you
don't actually hear yourself.

1573
01:23:01,844 --> 01:23:03,978
Well, I did.

1574
01:23:03,980 --> 01:23:07,681
And you're just like every other
gambler who comes onto your site.

1575
01:23:07,683 --> 01:23:11,685
You press it, when you should
have folded and moved on.

1576
01:23:11,687 --> 01:23:12,586
(BRAKES SCREECHING)

1577
01:23:14,589 --> 01:23:17,524
Later on,
when you're in prison,

1578
01:23:17,526 --> 01:23:20,094
that voice you'll be
hearing in your head

1579
01:23:20,096 --> 01:23:22,296
isn't your conscience,

1580
01:23:22,298 --> 01:23:24,331
